Hello guests and friends!  Our family is hosting Turo together. Tien Johnson, Lucky, and Kevin are our custodians taking care of the daily business. We became Turo host after so many trips of renting ourselves. We have traveled around the world to 76 countries. During our travels we received so much kindness from random strangers. We became kinder after each journey.  

One time, we walked by a beach park and saw a group of Egyptians in Alexandria grilling fish and bbq lamb. The smell was irresistible. We decided to walk back and forth until they invited us in. No shame, hehehe. And of course, that one time in a small suburb near Dijon in France, we had no GPS and could not find our Airbnb. We made a wrong turn into the private property of an old French famer. Between my husband and I, we could cover lots of languages but French; maybe not so much. The couple did not seem to understand there was a hotel in their town but recognized the last name when we showed them the address. They then jumped into their car and signaled us to follow them. After they guided us to the correct place, I said merci and tears came down so happy watching their car drove away into sunset on the mountain range. And believe it or not, we invited a random guest to have thanksgiving with us because he was alone in town during the holiday. That’s how we are and how we want our world to be.   

We have learned so much from hosting Turo. One guest gave us “Second City” tickets; others left chocolate. Those we kept. But we reached out to one guest who left a $3000 drone. We shipped it right back to him. We love to hear your stories about your first time in Chicago or coming back home to the Windy City for a visit. Please feel free to reach out. Facebook https://www.facebook.com/tien.t.chau
